  "title": "Senior Procurement Executive (Engineering) (Ref 26293)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Lead end-to-end procurement activities: sourcing, tendering, negotiation, contracting and purchase order management in accordance with Procurement Governance & Regulations.<br />• Identify reliable sources of supply for materials and services of require quality and quantity to be delivered on time.<br />• Carry out price analysis and conduct purchase/contract negotiation with vendors/suppliers to ensure materials/services are acquired at most competitive pricing.<br />• Build and maintain supplier relationships; perform supplier evaluation, qualification, and performance management.<br />• Liaise and collaborate with stakeholders on materials/services received and closing of PO.<br />• Provide regular feedback on materials/services status to stakeholders.<br />• Identify, explore, and implement innovative procurement strategies aligned with best practices.<br /><br />Requirements<br />• Bachelor Degree / Diploma in Purchasing / Electronics with minimum three years’ experience in similar position, preferably within project, M&E, construction or engineering industries.<br />• SAP S4 Hana working experience is a plus but not a must.<br />• Experienced in reviewing mechanical/ electrical design materials and bill of material (B.O.M)<br />• Excellent stakeholder engagement and interpersonal skills.<br />• Strong problem-solving capabilities to make sound and timely decisions in complex situations.<br />• Capable of working independently or collaboratively in a fast-paced environment.</p><p>Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
